## 🏛️ 1. System Architectural Overview
The Synchronized Distributed Administration Portal (SDAP) is engineered on a resilient, high-concurrency architecture tailored for enterprise campus ecosystems.
The application utilizes a decoupled, real-time backend controller loop coupled with a lightweight asynchronous frontend execution pipeline. This design isolates destructive schema mutations, manages atomic sequential transaction counters, and maintains strict role-based access control (RBAC).

