## 🔒 3. Anti-Tampering Shield & Security Layer
To prevent direct database manipulation via raw DB connections or outside administration tools, the architecture enforces a strict runtime database isolation layer.
Any schema mutating operation (UPDATE or DELETE) is structurally blocked unless an active application session initializes a signed session token: SET @application_auth_context = 'SECURE_CAMPUS_DESK_TOKEN_2026'.
## 3.1 Immutable Table Lock Triggers

CREATE TRIGGER trg_archive_bypass_update_lock 
BEFORE UPDATE ON deleted_records_archive FOR EACH ROW BEGIN
    IF (@application_auth_context IS NULL OR @application_auth_context != 'SECURE_CAMPUS_DESK_TOKEN_2026') THEN
        SIGNAL SQLSTATE '45000' SET MESSAGE_TEXT = 'Security Violation: Historic deletion archives are immutable and cannot be amended.';
    END IF;END;
CREATE TRIGGER trg_archive_bypass_delete_lock 
BEFORE DELETE ON deleted_records_archive FOR EACH ROW BEGIN
    IF (@application_auth_context IS NULL OR @application_auth_context != 'SECURE_CAMPUS_DESK_TOKEN_2026') THEN
        SIGNAL SQLSTATE '45000' SET MESSAGE_TEXT = 'Security Violation: Historic deletion archives are immutable and cannot be dropped.';
    END IF;END;

