## ☁️ 6. Cloud Handshake Sync Framework
Synchronization functions operate inside an outbound transaction query matrix.
When any internal data mutation is successfully executed, the system updates its synchronization flags: sync_status = 'Pending' and file_sync_status = 'Pending'.

[ Active Document / Booking Row Mutated ]
                  │
                  ▼
   [ Sets sync_status = 'Pending' ]
                  │
                  ▼
 [ Dashboard Action Sync Trigger Fired ]
                  │
                  ▼
 [ API executes compilePendingDatabaseChanges() ]
                  │
                  ▼
[ Data Chunks Encoded & Pushed across Secure SSL Tunnel ]
                  │
                  ▼
  [ Cloud Database Confirms Handshake ]
                  │
                  ▼
[ Local Flags cleared down to 'Synced' status ]

This bidirectional engine guarantees that records, hard deletions, and binary attachment assets are securely mirrored between the local network and the remote master cloud architecture without the risk of system data fragmentation or overlap crashes.
